Help Type: topic
Topic: overview

Overview

SpineDigest creates `.wikg` archives and exposes them as Wiki Graph object collections.

Core object commands:
  - A scope URI with `--query` finds URI-addressable objects.
  - A scope URI without `--query` enumerates URI-addressable objects.
  - An object URI reads one object.
  - `related` moves from one object to nearby objects.
  - `evidence` returns source-backed evidence.
  - `pack` builds bounded Agent-readable context around graph objects.

Generation tasks:
  - `reading-graph` builds the reading-oriented chunk graph.
  - `reading-summary` builds summaries from the Reading Graph.
  - `knowledge-graph` builds entity mentions from sourced text.

Queue tasks may call an LLM. Object inspection commands do not start generation.

URI routing:
  Use `wikigraph help uri` before constructing object command inputs.
